<br>
For example, I know this will look screwed up, but there are 20 distinct hits you can be hit for, lets say you take 200 hits and your spread looks like this.<br>
<br>
Case 1<br>
DI = 1 (10 hits)<br>
DI = 2 (10 hits)<br>
DI = 3 (10 hits)<br>
DI = 4 (10 hits)<br>
DI = 5 (10 hits)<br>
DI = 6 (10 hits)<br>
DI = 7 (10 hits)<br>
DI = 8 (10 hits)<br>
DI = 9 (10 hits)<br>
DI = 10 (10 hits)<br>
DI = 11 (10 hits)<br>
DI = 12 (10 hits)<br>
DI = 13 (10 hits)<br>
DI = 14 (10 hits)<br>
DI = 15 (10 hits)<br>
DI = 16 (10 hits)<br>
DI = 17 (10 hits)<br>
DI = 18 (10 hits)<br>
DI = 19 (10 hits)<br>
DI = 20 (10 hits)<br>
<br>
If you up your AC some you will see something like this<br>
<br>
Case 2<br>
DI = 1 (29 hits)<br>
DI = 2 (9 hits)<br>
DI = 3 (9 hits)<br>
DI = 4 (9 hits)<br>
DI = 5 (9 hits)<br>
DI = 6 (9 hits)<br>
DI = 7 (9 hits)<br>
DI = 8 (9 hits)<br>
DI = 9 (9 hits)<br>
DI = 10 (9 hits)<br>
DI = 11 (9 hits)<br>
DI = 12 (9 hits)<br>
DI = 13 (9 hits)<br>
DI = 14 (9 hits)<br>
DI = 15 (9 hits)<br>
DI = 16 (9 hits)<br>
DI = 17 (9 hits)<br>
DI = 18 (9 hits)<br>
DI = 19 (9 hits)<br>
DI = 20 (9 hits)<br>
<br>
In case 2, you look at 9 max hits (4.5% of 200)  as opossed to 10 (5% of 200) in case 1 and you say wow that ac only reduced my max hit % by 0.5%.  What your missing is its an even random distribution and you decreased DI=2 through 19 by that same 0.5%.  Your overall damage taken was just reduced by 9%.<br>
<br>
My hypothesis is that when your AC is equal to the mobs attack you get an equal percentage of hits in all 20 DI values.  When your AC is above the mobs ATK you get more min hits and all the other values decrease slightly.  When your AC is below the mobs ATK you get more max hits and all other values decrease slightly. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solinarinnoruuk>Solinar Innoruuk</A> at: 4/4/03 12:42:43 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mikar>Mikar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/4/03 2:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3094.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Brutall's ac test</span><hr size=1> Solinar<br>
