<br>
If this is the case, then one could hypothesize that the equilibrium of AC vs. ATK would be at the DI-distribution where the spikes at 1 and 20 were of equal size.<br>
<br>
To illustrate, imagine for a moment the distribution is 2% for each possible outcome in a range from -14 to 45 (50 distinct numbers), the DI distribution of a AC=ATK would in that case be:<br>
<br>
1: 32% (16 possibilities)<br>
2-19: 2% each (36% total)<br>
20: 32% (16 possibilities)<br>
<br>
Average hit on this mob would be: BD + 10.5*DI<br>
<br>
Let AC increase, or ATK decrease enough to push the mean down 2 units on our 1-20 scale, and you get:<br>
<br>
1: 36% (16+2 possibilities)<br>
2-19: 2% each (36% total)<br>
20: 28% (16-2 possibilities)<br>
<br>
Average hit would now be: BD + 9.74*DI<br>
<br>
Obviously, this could be vastly different depending on mobs DB/DI values.<br>
<br>
Mob1 - BD = 200, DI = 75 (min hit 275, max hit 1700)<br>
Mob2 - BD = 1000, DI = 35 (min hit 1035, max hit 1700)<br>
<br>
Mob1 at &quot;0&quot; ac/atk, average hit = 988<br>
Mob1 at &quot;-2&quot; ac/atk, average hit = 931<br>
<br>
AC's &quot;usefulness&quot; is a reduction in average damage of 5.8%<br>
<br>
Mob1 at &quot;0&quot; ac/atk, average hit = 1,368<br>
Mob1 at &quot;-2&quot; ac/atk, average hit = 1,341<br>
<br>
AC's &quot;usefulness&quot; is a reduction in average damage of 2.0% <p><big><center><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=370955 target=blank>Sage Aauminki Iceblade</a><br><a href=http://www.vazaelle.dk target=blank>Caer Cadarn</a></big><br>Vazaelle Server</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fatsow99>Fatsow99</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/4/03 6:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3094.topic&index=57>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: uh...</span><hr size=1> The distribution in between 2 and 19 is not flat, its a curve, although its rather flat. It also changes the more ac you get, just as min/max hits changes.<br>
